WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.742 --> 00:00:21.180
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:22.015 --> 00:00:29.922
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:35.360
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:35.429 --> 00:00:39.490
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:40.734 --> 00:00:45.637
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:46.373 --> 00:00:53.279
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you. right?</i>

7
00:00:54.681 --> 00:00:58.173
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:58.251 --> 00:01:05.157
<i>Leaving nothing behind.</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:05.292 --> 00:01:12.357
<i>In time. we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:12.432 --> 00:01:19.099
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks.</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:19.506 --> 00:01:29.074
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:02:01.748 --> 00:02:03.511
<i>Heh! It's over...</i>

13
00:02:06.586 --> 00:02:11.319
<i>Losing is not an Option</i>

14
00:02:12.726 --> 00:02:13.522
<i>What?!</i>

15
00:02:20.967 --> 00:02:21.797
<i>Just barely...</i>

16
00:02:22.235 --> 00:02:23.634
<i>That was a close one.</i>

17
00:02:24.404 --> 00:02:26.964
<i>But...I was able to throw it off</i>
<i>just a little.</i>

18
00:02:28.175 --> 00:02:29.403
<i>There's no mistake.</i>

19
00:02:30.544 --> 00:02:33.479
<i>He's now realized the secret</i>
<i>of the Byakugan.</i>

20
00:02:36.016 --> 00:02:38.610
<i>What's the meaning of this?</i>
<i>How?!</i>

21
00:02:43.724 --> 00:02:45.316
<i>How was he able to throw it</i>

22
00:02:45.392 --> 00:02:47.383
<i>a whole six inches</i>
<i>from his vital point?!</i>

23
00:02:55.302 --> 00:02:57.532
<i>I see... That Chakra!</i>

24
00:02:57.938 --> 00:03:01.101
<i>He was emitting Chakra</i>
<i>the whole time</i>

25
00:03:01.174 --> 00:03:03.233
<i>and covered the area surrounding him!</i>

26
00:03:04.544 --> 00:03:06.876
<i>And in a wide range to that extent.</i>

27
00:03:08.548 --> 00:03:10.743
<i>No wonder he was able</i>
<i>to detect the arrow and</i>

28
00:03:10.817 --> 00:03:13.911
<i>throw off the trajectory of it.</i>

29
00:03:17.824 --> 00:03:22.227
<i>But constantly emitting that</i>
<i>much Chakra is a death throe...</i>

30
00:03:23.830 --> 00:03:26.060
<i>If he doesn't go that far.</i>
<i>he can't dodge.</i>

31
00:03:26.433 --> 00:03:28.333
<i>In other words. there's no mistake.</i>

32
00:03:28.869 --> 00:03:30.200
<i>It's as I hypothesized...</i>

33
00:03:31.037 --> 00:03:34.803
<i>The arrow earlier was</i>
<i>totally invisible to him!</i>

34
00:03:36.710 --> 00:03:39.110
<i>He doesn't carry out useless attacks...</i>

35
00:03:39.446 --> 00:03:42.711
<i>And from the results.</i>
<i>he accurately examines the information.</i>

36
00:03:50.357 --> 00:03:53.724
<i>And...he's also discovered</i>
<i>the weakness of my eyes...</i>

37
00:03:53.894 --> 00:03:54.861
<i>Impressive.</i>

38
00:03:58.165 --> 00:04:00.463
<i>Of all the enemies</i>
<i>I've fought until now.</i>

39
00:04:00.734 --> 00:04:02.258
<i>this guy's the strongest!</i>

40
00:04:05.005 --> 00:04:07.303
<i>He has 360 degree sight.</i>

41
00:04:08.508 --> 00:04:11.068
<i>And he unfailingly detects attacks</i>

42
00:04:11.144 --> 00:04:14.773
<i>that penetrate the roughly</i>
<i>150 feeot circumference around him.</i>

43
00:04:16.383 --> 00:04:17.350
<i>But for some reason.</i>

44
00:04:17.417 --> 00:04:20.250
<i>there were Kunai Knives</i>
<i>he couldn't evade completely.</i>

45
00:04:22.189 --> 00:04:24.419
<i>Why couldn't he evade them?</i>

46
00:04:25.625 --> 00:04:28.253
<i>Because he couldn't see them!</i>

47
00:04:29.362 --> 00:04:33.731
<i>In other words. even his Visual Jutsu</i>
<i>has a slight blind spot!</i>

48
00:04:34.901 --> 00:04:38.098
<i>Being unable to see Kunai Knives</i>
<i>entering that blind spot.</i>

49
00:04:38.171 --> 00:04:39.433
<i>he's unable to react.</i>

50
00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:42.768
<i>So he was dealing with attacks</i>
<i>from the blind spot</i>

51
00:04:42.843 --> 00:04:45.073
<i>with that defense technique.</i>

52
00:04:45.946 --> 00:04:49.780
<i>And I analyzed all the attacks</i>
<i>I carried out</i>

53
00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:51.715
<i>and grasped them perfectly.</i>

54
00:04:52.752 --> 00:04:55.220
<i>Right behind his first thoracic vertebra...</i>

55
00:04:55.288 --> 00:04:58.724
<i>there exists a blind spot expanding</i>
<i>from a very small point.</i>

56
00:05:10.904 --> 00:05:13.702
<i>Indeed. if he moves and</i>
<i>doesn't stabiliz e the blind spot.</i>

57
00:05:13.773 --> 00:05:16.503
<i>it becomes difficult to aim there</i>
<i>with an arrow.</i>

58
00:05:16.843 --> 00:05:20.108
<i>But such a trick...doesn't fool me!</i>

59
00:05:23.083 --> 00:05:25.847
<i>Gentle Fist is pointless if</i>
<i>you don't come close to your enemy.</i>

60
00:05:26.253 --> 00:05:30.883
<i>And you can't afford to think about</i>
<i>approaching me at this point.</i>

61
00:05:31.458 --> 00:05:33.255
<i>It's about how to escape now...</i>

62
00:05:34.194 --> 00:05:38.460
<i>Though whether you struggle or not.</i>
<i>you're going to die anyway.</i>

63
00:05:44.337 --> 00:05:47.363
<i>Heh... It seems you only</i>
<i>have a little Chakra left.</i>

64
00:05:49.643 --> 00:05:51.702
<i>The fate of the small fry character</i>
<i>in an easy game</i>

65
00:05:51.778 --> 00:05:53.678
<i>is to be destroyed right away!</i>

66
00:05:57.717 --> 00:05:58.706
<i>It's useless!</i>

67
00:07:08.555 --> 00:07:09.681
<i>A thread?!</i>

68
00:07:11.191 --> 00:07:13.056
<i>I see. with this thread...</i>

69
00:07:17.831 --> 00:07:20.095
<i>This time. the trajectory was thrown off</i>
<i>slightly by the trees. huh?</i>

70
00:07:28.541 --> 00:07:30.133
<i>If that's the case...</i>

71
00:07:30.443 --> 00:07:33.412
<i>I'll add some rotation this time.</i>

72
00:07:34.014 --> 00:07:35.641
<i>So even if it hits a tree.</i>

73
00:07:35.715 --> 00:07:39.378
<i>it'll just cut through and the trajectory</i>
<i>won't be thrown off.</i>

74
00:07:39.619 --> 00:07:41.746
<i>And as before...</i>

75
00:07:41.888 --> 00:07:45.119
<i>I'll control the arrow up until</i>
<i>150 feet away from him</i>

76
00:07:45.191 --> 00:07:46.886
<i>using a thread with Chakra</i>
<i>flowing through.</i>

77
00:07:47.427 --> 00:07:49.554
<i>I'll take aim at the moving target...</i>

78
00:07:49.629 --> 00:07:52.723
<i>and plunge the arrow into</i>
<i>the blind spot with a pinpoint attack!</i>

79
00:07:56.970 --> 00:07:58.631
<i>He's still standing up?</i>

80
00:07:59.472 --> 00:08:03.169
<i>He's strong...</i>
<i>He's much stronger than me.</i>

81
00:08:04.844 --> 00:08:06.835
<i>I hardly have any Chakra left now.</i>

82
00:08:07.614 --> 00:08:10.640
<i>I probably won't be able to evade</i>
<i>his next attack completely.</i>

83
00:08:11.651 --> 00:08:12.845
<i>Is this it?</i>

84
00:08:15.321 --> 00:08:17.050
<i>I'll win no matter what!</i>

85
00:08:23.196 --> 00:08:25.892
<i>Naruto... I wonder what you'd do.</i>

86
00:08:28.868 --> 00:08:29.800
I've had enough.

87
00:08:32.072 --> 00:08:34.905
I can't dodge it anyway.

88
00:08:41.314 --> 00:08:44.374
<i>He's stopped moving...</i>
<i>Has he given up?</i>

89
00:08:45.452 --> 00:08:47.750
<i>But just to make doubly sure...</i>

90
00:08:48.455 --> 00:08:52.619
<i>Maximum destructive power</i>
<i>with 120% accuracy.</i>

91
00:09:14.447 --> 00:09:15.345
<i>I've got him!</i>

92
00:09:41.074 --> 00:09:42.200
<i>This is it.</i>

93
00:09:43.676 --> 00:09:44.506
<i>Gentle Fist!</i>

94
00:10:20.046 --> 00:10:23.038
<i>Wh What? He still... ?!</i>

95
00:10:23.483 --> 00:10:27.283
<i>No! My attack just now</i>
<i>should've made the kill.</i>

96
00:10:27.954 --> 00:10:30.320
<i>Substance with Chakra base...</i>

97
00:10:30.390 --> 00:10:32.517
<i>It's meaningless against Gentle Fist.</i>

98
00:10:33.860 --> 00:10:35.088
<i>Gentle Fist...</i>

99
00:10:35.161 --> 00:10:37.129
<i>I see. in his final moments.</i>

100
00:10:37.197 --> 00:10:39.631
<i>he funneled the last Chakra</i>
<i>through the thread!</i>

101
00:10:48.942 --> 00:10:49.806
<i>Eight crows...</i>

102
00:10:52.679 --> 00:10:54.442
<i>Again I couldn't see one of them.</i>

103
00:10:59.018 --> 00:11:00.110
<i>What happened to him?</i>

104
00:11:08.528 --> 00:11:10.792
<i>He damaged several of</i>
<i>my internal organs.</i>

105
00:11:11.231 --> 00:11:13.563
<i>But...I can still move.</i>

106
00:11:22.609 --> 00:11:23.940
<i>You failure...</i>

107
00:11:25.578 --> 00:11:31.983
<i>I told you... I don't know when to quit!</i>

108
00:11:34.420 --> 00:11:37.947
<i>Why do you try to go against</i>
<i>your destiny that much?</i>

109
00:11:38.925 --> 00:11:43.089
<i>Because I was called...a failure!</i>

110
00:11:46.499 --> 00:11:50.060
<i>But if you're going to say it's futile.</i>
<i>you don't have to do anything!</i>

111
00:11:50.303 --> 00:11:55.036
<i>After I become the Hokage.</i>
<i>I'll change Hyuga!</i>

112
00:11:56.776 --> 00:11:58.801
<i>The Ninjutsu that you're good at. huh?</i>

113
00:11:59.712 --> 00:12:00.940
<i>I was careless...</i>

114
00:12:02.515 --> 00:12:07.782
<i>Clone Jutsu was the Ninjutsu</i>
<i>I stunk at.</i>

115
00:12:10.590 --> 00:12:14.492
<i>Don't be whining about boring stuff</i>
<i>like destiny and what not.</i>

116
00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:17.393
<i>and how it can't be changed!</i>

117
00:12:18.064 --> 00:12:20.532
<i>Unlike me.</i>

118
00:12:20.867 --> 00:12:22.528
<i>you're not a failure.</i>

119
00:12:27.073 --> 00:12:28.199
<i>Naruto...</i>

120
00:12:28.741 --> 00:12:31.403
Now it's become the three of us...

121
00:12:32.178 --> 00:12:34.112
Don't worry about such things.

122
00:12:34.514 --> 00:12:36.744
Both Choji and Neji will
catch up right away.

123
00:12:40.253 --> 00:12:42.084
Choji had the trump card.

124
00:12:42.922 --> 00:12:47.018
And I've fought Neji
in the Chunin exam. so I know...

125
00:12:47.794 --> 00:12:48.658
Know what?

126
00:12:50.463 --> 00:12:54.923
That he's... a true genius. Believe it!

127
00:12:57.737 --> 00:12:59.500
<i>I cannot lose...</i>

128
00:13:00.873 --> 00:13:03.535
<i>Whether he's an enemy</i>
<i>much stronger than me...</i>

129
00:13:03.609 --> 00:13:05.338
<i>or even if this body should fail me...</i>

130
00:13:05.912 --> 00:13:07.641
<i>I cannot lose!</i>

131
00:13:10.283 --> 00:13:13.741
<i>I have a reason why I cannot lose!</i>

132
00:13:26.132 --> 00:13:29.067
<i>I've had a hard time of it this time.</i>

133
00:13:33.239 --> 00:13:34.501
<i>I played too long...</i>

134
00:13:35.575 --> 00:13:36.166
<i>Huh?</i>

135
00:14:04.771 --> 00:14:06.568
<i>I can't build up Chakra...</i>

136
00:14:06.773 --> 00:14:09.207
How? You should've
been instantly killed!

137
00:14:09.842 --> 00:14:11.207
How come you're alive?!

138
00:14:11.778 --> 00:14:13.973
I couldn't completely
evade it anyway.

139
00:14:15.114 --> 00:14:18.242
So I was prepared to deliberately
take the hit.

140
00:14:19.619 --> 00:14:23.419
And I knew of my own weakness
much more than you do...

141
00:14:24.557 --> 00:14:27.390
<i>There were eight crows. huh?</i>

142
00:14:28.761 --> 00:14:30.820
This Byakugan has a blind spot.

143
00:14:31.798 --> 00:14:35.928
However. if I knew that your attack
would only come from there...

144
00:14:36.436 --> 00:14:40.065
I could release my Chakra just
to that blind spot and detect the attack.

145
00:14:40.606 --> 00:14:42.164
It's not so difficult to make

146
00:14:42.241 --> 00:14:45.699
a move of just a few inches
to throw off the aim.

147
00:14:46.345 --> 00:14:49.007
I'd suffer a serious injury.
but instant death can be avoided.

148
00:14:53.586 --> 00:14:55.486
So you took the hit deliberately...?

149
00:14:55.555 --> 00:14:57.853
It doesn't change the fact
that you're going to die here.

150
00:14:59.091 --> 00:15:00.820
How can you go that far?!

151
00:15:02.595 --> 00:15:07.362
"Of all the enemies."
you're the strongest I've ever fought...

152
00:15:08.601 --> 00:15:12.002
But. there's a reason why I cannot lose.

153
00:15:14.574 --> 00:15:21.343
Of all those I've ever fought.
the strongest one said this to me...

154
00:15:24.784 --> 00:15:28.686
- Unlike me... you are not a failure!
- <i>Unlike me...you are not a failure!</i>

155
00:15:30.323 --> 00:15:31.187
He said that.

156
00:15:33.392 --> 00:15:35.553
I've been called a genius all along.

157
00:15:36.696 --> 00:15:38.823
So I cannot lose.

158
00:15:40.032 --> 00:15:41.897
And for the sake of those guys
who believe

159
00:15:41.968 --> 00:15:44.937
that this humdrum and small me
is a genius!

160
00:15:54.413 --> 00:15:56.973
"The fate of the small fry character
in a game is to be destroyed right away."

161
00:15:57.450 --> 00:15:58.849
You said that. didn't you?

162
00:16:09.795 --> 00:16:11.387
Look at this situation!

163
00:16:14.934 --> 00:16:18.768
Things like fate.
isn't determined by someone!

164
00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:25.641
I wonder...

165
00:16:26.212 --> 00:16:28.874
You also look like
you're going to die!

166
00:16:35.321 --> 00:16:37.949
<i>Neji. live.</i>

167
00:16:38.524 --> 00:16:40.617
<i>More than anyone in the clan.</i>

168
00:16:40.693 --> 00:16:43.253
<i>you're the man loved most</i>
<i>by the Hyuga ability...</i>

169
00:16:46.632 --> 00:16:51.092
I cannot die so easily.

170
00:16:53.506 --> 00:16:57.670
Even if you act tough.
you can't stem the current now...

171
00:16:58.511 --> 00:17:02.675
Master Sasuke ran to
the Sound Village by his own wish.

172
00:17:09.221 --> 00:17:12.349
<i>Sasuke is now in the darkness...</i>

173
00:17:20.066 --> 00:17:20.964
No...

174
00:17:23.669 --> 00:17:28.402
<i>Naruto... You've got better eyes than me.</i>

175
00:17:30.343 --> 00:17:35.781
There's a person who can find him
in the darkness and save him.

176
00:17:37.950 --> 00:17:40.316
Master Sasuke belongs
to Lord Orochimaru.

177
00:17:43.222 --> 00:17:45.588
No matter who it may be.
they can't save...

178
00:17:45.658 --> 00:17:46.647
He <i>can</i> save him!

179
00:17:54.166 --> 00:17:58.762
<i>Because...Naruto...you...</i>

180
00:18:02.241 --> 00:18:05.233
<i>You saved me from the darkness!</i>

181
00:18:15.488 --> 00:18:17.251
Talking rubbish until the end...

182
00:18:20.660 --> 00:18:21.592
<i>But...</i>

183
00:18:22.695 --> 00:18:26.722
<i>I haven't been pushed this far</i>
<i>since Kimimaro.</i>

184
00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:36.365
<i>Damn it...</i>

185
00:19:49.081 --> 00:19:49.979
<i>Everyone...</i>

186
00:19:55.755 --> 00:19:56.813
<i>I'll leave the rest...</i>

187
00:19:58.157 --> 00:19:59.419
<i>to you.</i>

188
00:21:25.578 --> 00:21:27.978
<i>For the first time. I spoke to you</i>

189
00:21:28.047 --> 00:21:31.073
<i>And you smiled</i>

190
00:21:31.317 --> 00:21:33.615
<i>For the first time. I was able to speak</i>

191
00:21:33.686 --> 00:21:36.416
<i>In my own words</i>

192
00:21:36.488 --> 00:21:42.051
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

193
00:21:42.394 --> 00:21:47.593
<i>Despite my doubts.</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

194
00:21:47.867 --> 00:21:53.271
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

195
00:21:53.472 --> 00:21:59.001
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

196
00:21:59.979 --> 00:22:05.178
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

197
00:22:05.584 --> 00:22:12.251
<i>But you don't feel anything for me. do you?</i>

198
00:22:12.758 --> 00:22:15.454
<i>I feel so sad</i>

199
00:22:15.527 --> 00:22:16.425
<i>But...</i>

200
00:22:16.495 --> 00:22:18.895
<i>For the first time. I spoke to you</i>

201
00:22:18.964 --> 00:22:21.933
<i>And you smiled</i>

202
00:22:22.067 --> 00:22:24.661
<i>For the first time. I was able to speak</i>

203
00:22:24.737 --> 00:22:27.729
<i>In my own words</i>

204
00:22:27.907 --> 00:22:30.239
<i>For the first time. I spoke to you</i>

205
00:22:30.309 --> 00:22:33.437
<i>And you smiled</i>

206
00:22:33.512 --> 00:22:35.980
<i>For the first time. I was able to speak</i>

207
00:22:36.048 --> 00:22:38.949
<i>In my own words</i>

208
00:22:39.018 --> 00:22:43.580
<i>For the first time. I spoke to you</i>

209
00:22:52.631 --> 00:22:55.293
Yahoo! The enemies are quite close!

210
00:22:55.367 --> 00:22:57.631
All right! We'll catch up in a burst!

211
00:22:57.703 --> 00:22:59.295
Speaking in terms of number.
we've got more!

212
00:22:59.371 --> 00:23:00.963
If things go well.
we can get him back next!

213
00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:03.804
Yeah! I don't feel like losing
with four against two!

214
00:23:03.943 --> 00:23:04.807
Four against two?

215
00:23:04.877 --> 00:23:05.866
That's twice the opponents' number!

216
00:23:05.945 --> 00:23:07.412
Say say. Were there four of us?

217
00:23:07.479 --> 00:23:11.245
Are you an idiot?!
